# Detail Page Layout

Detail pages (entity detail views, e.g. Master Customer detail, Super Admin detail) MUST use the same layout structure for consistency across the app.

## Requirements

### 1. Page Structure

**Every detail page MUST have:**

- **Header section:** Page title (entity name) and breadcrumbs in a flex column.
- **Data card:** A single main `Card` containing the entity’s detail information.
- Optional: Additional cards below (e.g. "Daftar SPK" table) when the entity has related lists.

### 2. Data Card Layout

**The main data card MUST use this structure:**

```tsx
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Data [Entity Name]</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <div className="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[250px_1fr]">
      {/* Profile / Avatar column (left) */}
      <div className="flex justify-center">
        <Avatar className="size-48">
          <AvatarImage src={...} alt={...} />
          <AvatarFallback>
            <UserIcon className="text-muted-foreground size-24" />
          </AvatarFallback>
        </Avatar>
      </div>

      {/* Detail content (right) */}
      <div className="space-y-8">
        {/* Section 1, Section 2, ... */}
      </div>
    </div>
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

- **Grid:** `grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[250px_1fr]` — avatar column 250px, content takes remaining space.
- **Avatar column:** Centered with `flex justify-center`. Avatar size `size-48`, fallback icon `size-24` with `text-muted-foreground`.
- **Content column:** Use `space-y-8` between sections.

### 3. Section Structure (Detail blocks)

**Each logical section (e.g. "Detail Customer", "Detail Kontak") MUST follow:**

```tsx
<div className="space-y-4">
  {/* Section title: icon + heading */}
  <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
    <SectionIcon className="text-destructive size-6" />
    <h2 className="text-destructive text-lg font-semibold">
      [Section Title]
    </h2>
  </div>

  {/* Fields in two-column grid */}
  <div className="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
    <div className="space-y-2">
      <label className="text-muted-foreground text-sm font-medium">
        [Field Label]
      </label>
      <p className="text-base">[Field Value]</p>
    </div>
    {/* ... more fields */}
  </div>
</div>
```

- **Section title:** Icon (`text-destructive size-6`) + `h2` (`text-destructive text-lg font-semibold`), wrapped in `flex items-center gap-3`.
- **Fields:** `grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2`. Each field: `space-y-2`, label with `text-muted-foreground text-sm font-medium`, value with `p className="text-base"`.

### 4. Typography and Colors

- **Card title:** `CardTitle` (e.g. "Data Customer", "Data Super Admin").
- **Section titles:** Red/destructive: `text-destructive text-lg font-semibold` and icon `text-destructive size-6`.
- **Labels:** `text-muted-foreground text-sm font-medium`.
- **Values:** `text-base` (default text color).

### 5. Skeleton for Detail Card

**Loading state MUST mirror this layout** (see skeleton-loader rule):

- Same grid: avatar column (centered circular skeleton `size-48`) and content column.
- For each section: skeleton for icon + title line, then a two-column grid of label/value skeletons matching field count.

### 6. Reference Implementations

Use these as the source of truth for structure and class names:

- `apps/web/app/(dashboard)/super-admin/[slug]/page.tsx` — Data Super Admin card.
- `apps/web/app/(dashboard)/master-customer/[id]/page.tsx` — Data Customer card (with multiple sections: Detail Customer, Detail Kontak).

